And this was a big hill
that I had to get up now,

00:12:41.760 --> 00:12:43.162
because we were down
in the gulch.

00:12:43.195 --> 00:12:46.265
And we had ice that,
for a week--

00:12:46.298 --> 00:12:50.736
so we could slide
on cardboard.

00:12:50.769 --> 00:12:52.171
That's what we slid on,

00:12:52.204 --> 00:12:55.007
but we had ice that we'd take
buckets of water,

00:12:55.040 --> 00:12:59.745
"No one will ever get up this."

00:12:59.778 --> 00:13:03.115
So Fat Louie is going,
"Here we go."

00:13:03.148 --> 00:13:05.484
I get up to it.
I get about halfway up,

00:13:05.517 --> 00:13:10.189
and I go, "I am losing my grip,
I'm losing my grip."

00:13:10.222 --> 00:13:11.790
And I just go on my back
and go down.

00:13:11.823 --> 00:13:14.960
Whee!

00:13:14.993 --> 00:13:16.461
I did it, like, three or four
times,

00:13:16.494 --> 00:13:20.332
'cause I just go, "I'm just
gonna enjoy this."

00:13:20.365 --> 00:13:22.601
And then finally I got up to
the very top,

00:13:22.634 --> 00:13:23.802
and there was a road.

00:13:23.835 --> 00:13:26.338
That's right--
there's my house.

00:13:26.371 --> 00:13:29.641
And the neighbor came by.

00:13:29.674 --> 00:13:31.810
"Hey!

00:13:31.843 --> 00:13:33.378
Are you guys okay?"

00:13:33.411 --> 00:13:37.149
"Everything's perfect!

00:13:37.182 --> 00:13:39.952
We got it!
Go ahead!"

00:13:39.985 --> 00:13:41.520
"You sure you don't need
any help?

00:13:41.553 --> 00:13:43.222
"We don't need any help!"

00:13:43.255 --> 00:13:45.958
That was my role in the family.

00:13:45.991 --> 00:13:49.962
Deflect, deflect, deflect.

00:13:49.995 --> 00:13:53.832
"We don't need any help.
It's under control.

00:13:53.865 --> 00:13:56.902
Someone shot our tires out!"

00:14:00.105 --> 00:14:02.074
I didn't want those people
to help,

00:14:02.107 --> 00:14:04.042
'cause it's a family thing,
in families.

00:14:04.075 --> 00:14:06.912
It's your dad;
it's your situation.

00:14:06.945 --> 00:14:12.017
It's your family.
You went into the woods.

00:14:12.050 --> 00:14:13.852
It's not even explainable,
really.

00:14:13.885 --> 00:14:16.188
It's just...

00:14:16.221 --> 00:14:18.090
We finally get up it
across the street,

00:14:18.123 --> 00:14:20.158
and I go in the house.

00:14:20.191 --> 00:14:22.661
And my brother Roger is there.

00:14:22.694 --> 00:14:24.930
"What's going on?"

00:14:24.963 --> 00:14:26.064
Dad drove into the woods.

00:14:26.097 --> 00:14:29.234
"Oh, for God sakes."

00:14:29.267 --> 00:14:32.037
Everybody has that voice in our
family, so...

00:14:32.070 --> 00:14:34.874
Even mom.
"Oh, my God."

00:14:36.241 --> 00:14:38.710
My mom was really mad.
She was...

00:14:38.743 --> 00:14:40.913
She just went...
"Mm."

00:14:45.417 --> 00:14:48.086
And said to my brother,
"Go get him. Go get him."

00:14:48.119 --> 00:14:51.056
Tommy's in there.
I tell him to stay.

00:14:51.089 --> 00:14:52.858
I said, "Don't get out, Tommy.

00:14:52.891 --> 00:14:56.128
Just stay with Dad."

00:14:56.161 --> 00:14:59.898
And then, he went in, and he
was able to drive the car out.

00:14:59.931 --> 00:15:02.234
My dad--they brought my dad in.

00:15:02.267 --> 00:15:03.936
He was drunk, so drunk.

00:15:04.636 --> 00:15:06.071
Sat in the chair.

00:15:06.104 --> 00:15:08.206
I was sitting there because
when you're 11

00:15:08.239 --> 00:15:09.608
you have to think about stuff
but you can't really

00:15:09.641 --> 00:15:14.813
contemplate it very well.
You just go, "Huh.

00:15:14.846 --> 00:15:18.917
"I'm starving.

00:15:18.950 --> 00:15:23.555
Should I eat the egg?

00:15:23.588 --> 00:15:27.092
My dad rustles out of his
deep, you know,

00:15:27.125 --> 00:15:29.461
drunken stupor.

00:15:34.599 --> 00:15:36.234
[groans deeply]

00:15:36.267 --> 00:15:39.571
[coughs aggressively]

00:15:39.604 --> 00:15:42.774
He's alive. He lives.

00:15:42.807 --> 00:15:46.111
My brother, Rog, is standing
right next to him.

00:15:46.144 --> 00:15:49.114
He goes, "Hey, buddy.

00:15:49.147 --> 00:15:52.517
"Hey, you wanna go to Joe's
with me?

00:15:52.550 --> 00:15:55.654
And get some bulk oil?"

00:15:55.687 --> 00:15:59.291
And I never got to go with
my dad again on any trip alone.

00:15:59.324 --> 00:16:02.160
I hope you enjoyed that.
Thank you so much.

00:16:02.193 --> 00:16:03.996
[cheers and applause]

00:16:04.029 --> 00:16:07.366
I love you, Dad!
Love you, Mom!

00:16:07.399 --> 00:16:11.536
Forgive your dad.
He didn't mean it.

